# Project Rules

## SYSTEM RULE — PRODUCTION FIRST (CRITICAL)

**Any change (frontend OR backend) MUST be deployed to production immediately. NO EXCEPTIONS.**

### FORBIDDEN

- Writing code without deploy
- Reporting "done" without deploy
- Testing locally only
- Leaving production server outdated

### REQUIRED FLOW (after code changes)

1. `git add .`
2. `git commit -m "..."`  
3. `git push origin main`

### DEPLOY (mandatory after ANY changes)

**Single command only** (backend + frontend):

```bash
ssh root@85.117.235.93 "bash /var/www/deploy-cheepy.sh"
```

### DEPLOY SCRIPT — READ-ONLY (ABSOLUTE RULE)

- ❌ NEVER MODIFY `deploy/deploy-cheepy.sh` (except git status check)
- ❌ NEVER ADD LOGIC TO DEPLOY (no extra git pull, patch, custom scripts)
- ✔ ONLY RUN deploy

### SERVER CONSISTENCY LOCK (NO UNTRACKED FILES EVER)

- Server must ALWAYS match Git
- ❌ NO untracked files on server
- ❌ NO manual files, NO server-only code
- ✔ `git status` on server → clean (nothing to commit, working tree clean)
- If server not clean: `git fetch origin && git reset --hard origin/main && git clean -fd`

Or on server directly: `bash /var/www/deploy-cheepy.sh`

Nginx root: `/var/www/siteaacess.store/dist`.

Apply Laravel patches from `docs/infrastructure/laravel/` to the live app when API fixes are doc-only in this repo.

### VERIFICATION (mandatory)

- Open production URL
- DevTools Network: no 500 / no unexpected 401
- Manually test the feature

### REPORT MUST INCLUDE

- Commit hash(es)
- Deploy command output (or summary)
- Confirmation production works

**If not deployed → task is NOT done.**

---

## SSH — Production

**SSH:** `ssh root@85.117.235.93`

- Use for server builds, nginx reload, Laravel artisan, logs.
